The paper deals with a problem of finding minimum centers in a tree to cover uncertain points, which involves algorithms and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The problem also involves probability and optimization, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Game Theory). Finally, the problem can be applied to various real-world scenarios, such as facility location and network design, which are related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
